This paper discusses the impact of artificial intelligence on the future of work, which is a topic that falls under the category of AI. The paper also explores the skills and capabilities required by humans and AI systems, which is related to human-computer interaction (HCI) and machine learning (LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the relevance of autonomy and generality of AI systems, which is related to the sub-categories of social and information sciences (SI) and cybernetics (CY).
